      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "Yes, those are the default configurations for each slot.\n\nYou can try increasing the number of pads to see what fits. Make sure to update the [yaml config](https://github.com/wafer-space/gf180mcu-project-template/tree/main/librelane/slots) for your slot accordingly.\n\nHowever, you need to consider both the minimum pitch of the bondpads and the capabilities of your PCB supplier.\nThis depends on the bonding service you are targeting and where you manufacture your PCB.",
